616
00:14:25.090 --> 00:14:27.760
There's no way that's true!

617
00:14:27.760 --> 00:14:30.430
He would never kill Vivi's dad!

618
00:14:33.020 --> 00:14:36.690
Sabo would never do something like that!

619
00:14:37.310 --> 00:14:38.480
Of course.

620
00:14:38.750 --> 00:14:40.860
I agree with you.

621
00:14:40.860 --> 00:14:44.240
The Revolutionary Army's
enemies are the world nobles.

622
00:14:44.240 --> 00:14:46.200
Not the kings!

623
00:14:46.530 --> 00:14:50.330
"Revolutionary Army Declares
War on Celestial Dragons"...

624
00:14:50.330 --> 00:14:55.670
"Chief of Staff Sabo Assassinates
King Cobra of Alabasta"?!

625
00:14:55.670 --> 00:15:00.380
"Disappearance of Alabasta's
Royal Daughter, Princess Vivi"?!

626
00:15:01.800 --> 00:15:05.010
Where are you and how are
you feeling, my darling Vivi?!

627
00:15:05.010 --> 00:15:07.390
Please be safe!

628
00:15:07.800 --> 00:15:09.930
Set sail for Alabasta!

629
00:15:09.930 --> 00:15:10.970
Now!

630
00:15:10.970 --> 00:15:14.180
King Cobra is already dead.

631
00:15:14.180 --> 00:15:15.850
What would be the point?

632
00:15:15.850 --> 00:15:19.820
And Vivi disappeared in
Mary Geoise, of all places.

633
00:15:19.820 --> 00:15:21.020
Then...

634
00:15:21.440 --> 00:15:22.990
we're going to Mary Geoise!

635
00:15:22.990 --> 00:15:23.690
What?

636
00:15:23.690 --> 00:15:26.820
What?! Are they going to Mary Geoise?

637
00:15:26.820 --> 00:15:28.780
I'm in trouble...

638
00:15:28.780 --> 00:15:31.080
I can't really hear them!

639
00:15:33.660 --> 00:15:36.210
That's our enemies' stronghold, idiot!

640
00:15:36.210 --> 00:15:38.630
Do you plan to take on Marine Headquarters?!

641
00:15:38.630 --> 00:15:39.840
Damn right!

642
00:15:39.840 --> 00:15:42.550
What, are you scared, Zoro?!

643
00:15:42.550 --> 00:15:44.880
I'm just saying we have no leads!

644
00:15:44.880 --> 00:15:46.260
Calm down!

645
00:15:48.260 --> 00:15:51.220
Vivi's father is dead?!

646
00:15:51.720 --> 00:15:56.640
He was so nice to us
even though we're pirates...!

647
00:15:57.390 --> 00:16:00.110
I'd like to thank you...

648
00:16:00.610 --> 00:16:05.820
from the bottom of my heart as a father
and as a resident of this land.

649
00:16:07.360 --> 00:16:09.160
Thank you very much.

650
00:16:13.120 --> 00:16:17.000
Yeah! No other king is that kind!

651
00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:19.210
Vivi!

652
00:16:19.540 --> 00:16:21.380
I'm so worried!

653
00:16:21.380 --> 00:16:23.380
This must be so hard for her!

654
00:16:23.380 --> 00:16:24.840
I can't help but worry!

655
00:16:24.840 --> 00:16:27.010
Vivi!

656
00:16:27.010 --> 00:16:29.340
– Vivi!
– Vivi!

657
00:16:29.340 --> 00:16:33.720
It seems like the last Reverie
was quite tumultuous.

658
00:16:33.720 --> 00:16:38.690
I've never heard a single shady rumor about
the Kingdom of Alabasta's government.

659
00:16:38.690 --> 00:16:43.520
The Revolutionary Army's
chief of staff, Sabo...

660
00:16:46.940 --> 00:16:51.870
We met that big brother of yours
in Dressrosa, didn't we, Luffy?

661
00:16:51.870 --> 00:16:54.870
I can't take it! I'm worried about Vivi!

662
00:16:54.870 --> 00:16:56.620
Where is she?!

663
00:16:56.620 --> 00:16:59.620
Me, too! Alright! Let's go rescue her!

664
00:16:59.620 --> 00:17:01.250
Let's go!

665
00:17:01.250 --> 00:17:03.170
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

666
00:17:03.170 --> 00:17:06.170
That's enough, you guys!

667
00:17:07.630 --> 00:17:08.760
Luffy!

668
00:17:09.220 --> 00:17:10.720
What did you say...

669
00:17:10.720 --> 00:17:13.100
when Ace was in trouble?

670
00:17:17.180 --> 00:17:19.770
Ace has his own adventures.

671
00:17:22.230 --> 00:17:27.110
You trusted him to pull through
on his own until he actually needed help.

672
00:17:30.070 --> 00:17:32.780
Are you underestimating Vivi?

673
00:17:32.780 --> 00:17:35.240
She can take care of herself!

674
00:17:35.700 --> 00:17:40.290
When the time comes for us to step in,
we'll give one hell of a fight!

675
00:17:40.870 --> 00:17:43.750
We can't do anything now,
so stop making a fuss!

676
00:17:46.000 --> 00:17:48.920
All we can do is make a fuss,
so let us make a fuss!

677
00:17:48.920 --> 00:17:51.130
This guy's an oni!

678
00:17:51.130 --> 00:17:52.680
You Onigashima!

679
00:17:52.680 --> 00:17:54.050
Green Kaido!

680
00:17:54.050 --> 00:17:55.390
Green Mom!

681
00:17:55.390 --> 00:17:56.890
Shitty Moss Head!

682
00:17:56.890 --> 00:17:58.140
– Boo!
– Boo!

683
00:17:58.470 --> 00:18:01.270
– Boo! Boo! Boo!
– Boo! Boo! Boo!

684
00:18:01.270 --> 00:18:02.940
Shut up, number four.

685
00:18:03.940 --> 00:18:06.020
Again with this?!

686
00:18:06.020 --> 00:18:09.690
It's not so easy being above you!

687
00:18:11.110 --> 00:18:14.490
Since when are you above me?!

688
00:18:14.490 --> 00:18:18.290
Always have been and always will be!

689
00:18:22.290 --> 00:18:27.090
While we were in Wano,
so many incidents have occurred,

690
00:18:27.090 --> 00:18:30.260
and they're developing rapidly...

691
00:18:32.260 --> 00:18:34.090
The abolition of the Warlords...

692
00:18:34.550 --> 00:18:37.640
sent those elite pirates back to sea.

693
00:18:38.560 --> 00:18:39.720
And that led to...

694
00:18:41.100 --> 00:18:43.390
the foundation of Cross Guild,

695
00:18:44.560 --> 00:18:48.730
and Buggy the Bombastic Clown's
ascension as a new Emperor!

696
00:18:49.480 --> 00:18:52.110
That last one's gotta be a mistake!

697
00:18:52.530 --> 00:18:56.990
Maybe it is and maybe it isn't.

698
00:18:59.160 --> 00:19:00.370
Thanks!

699
00:19:00.700 --> 00:19:01.410
Luffy.

700
00:19:03.290 --> 00:19:08.040
There are a few other names in here
that have connections to you...

701
00:19:08.040 --> 00:19:09.420
Do you want to hear?

702
00:19:12.710 --> 00:19:14.720
I'll leave it to you.

703
00:19:14.720 --> 00:19:16.760
Just tell me the important ones!

704
00:19:17.260 --> 00:19:18.510
All right.

705
00:19:18.510 --> 00:19:19.680
Let's do that.

706
00:19:20.510 --> 00:19:23.020
You've already got a lot on your mind.

707
00:19:28.610 --> 00:19:30.690
Sabo is innocent!

708
00:19:34.360 --> 00:19:35.700
He...

709
00:19:36.110 --> 00:19:38.320
grew up in a strict home,

710
00:19:38.320 --> 00:19:41.160
so he just wants to set everyone free!

711
00:19:45.730 --> 00:19:48.920
We gotta set out to sea someday!

712
00:19:48.920 --> 00:19:52.090
Let's get out of this country and live free!

713
00:19:52.090 --> 00:19:56.630
I wanna see the world out there
and write a book about it!

714
00:19:56.630 --> 00:19:59.550
Navigation is the one thing I do love to study!

715
00:19:59.550 --> 00:20:02.720
Let's get even stronger
and become pirates someday!

716
00:20:08.730 --> 00:20:12.400
That was my plan anyway!
You don't have to tell me twice!

717
00:20:12.400 --> 00:20:18.240
When I'm a pirate, I'll beat up everyone
and become the biggest, baddest one of all!

718
00:20:18.740 --> 00:20:21.830
That's how I'll leave my mark on the world!

719
00:20:22.660 --> 00:20:28.750
It doesn't matter if the whole world
rejects or despises me,

720
00:20:28.750 --> 00:20:31.670
I'll become a great pirate and show them all!

721
00:20:32.500 --> 00:20:35.510
I won't run from anyone!
I won't lose to anyone!

722
00:20:35.510 --> 00:20:40.390
Whether I'm feared or hated or whatever,
my name will be known all over!

723
00:20:44.850 --> 00:20:46.270
We made an oath.

724
00:20:46.270 --> 00:20:49.310
The three of us, including Ace!

725
00:20:51.770 --> 00:20:53.270
I got it!

726
00:20:53.270 --> 00:20:55.440
Alright!

727
00:20:56.780 --> 00:20:59.360
I'm gonna...

728
00:20:59.740 --> 00:21:01.490
I'm gonna...

729
00:21:09.830 --> 00:21:11.250
What did you just say?

730
00:21:11.250 --> 00:21:12.210
What?

731
00:21:14.130 --> 00:21:16.550
That's so funny!

732
00:21:16.550 --> 00:21:20.340
Hey! No, no, no... No way!

733
00:21:21.260 --> 00:21:22.510
I love it!

734
00:21:22.510 --> 00:21:24.220
That's great!

735
00:21:25.930 --> 00:21:28.390
Hey, Chopper. Examine his head!

736
00:21:30.600 --> 00:21:32.230
No way!

737
00:21:32.230 --> 00:21:34.400
That's impossible!

738
00:21:35.480 --> 00:21:38.320
Maybe it's possible once
I'm King of the Pirates!

739
00:21:38.320 --> 00:21:41.070
No one would think something like that...

740
00:21:41.740 --> 00:21:42.740
Huh?

741
00:21:42.740 --> 00:21:44.320
Didn't I tell you?

742
00:21:44.740 --> 00:21:45.830
Any of you?

743
00:21:46.410 --> 00:21:50.040
Well, I don't care if you didn't...
Because that's impossible!

744
00:21:51.250 --> 00:21:55.590
I guess I only told Shanks, Ace, and Sabo.

745
00:21:57.090 --> 00:21:58.840
What did they say?

746
00:21:58.840 --> 00:22:01.010
They just laughed.

747
00:22:02.720 --> 00:22:05.760
Shanks laughed himself to tears.

748
00:22:18.530 --> 00:22:22.570
That's what I want at the end of my dream.

749
00:22:48.330 --> 00:22:50.900
"Time's up, won't come back"

750
00:22:52.290 --> 00:22:55.260
Somebody said again, with a laugh

751
00:22:56.410 --> 00:23:00.590
Fine then, guess time for hide-and-seek's...

752
00:23:01.620 --> 00:23:02.420
...over now

753
00:23:03.840 --> 00:23:07.820
Let's go, come on
(We can see it soon)

754
00:23:07.880 --> 00:23:11.580
Our heartbeats were meant to sound out
(Our island)

755
00:23:11.740 --> 00:23:15.840
Things will soon change, wait and see
(We can see it soon)

756
00:23:15.860 --> 00:23:19.700
Get stronger, despair no longer, you still have time to spare
(1-2-3)

757
00:23:19.940 --> 00:23:21.130
Let's raise that dream

758
00:23:21.130 --> 00:23:28.150
Living off just grief and solitude, it can't sustain a soul like mine, oh no

759
00:23:28.150 --> 00:23:32.070
When we were young, we were so carefree, that's all done now

760
00:23:32.120 --> 00:23:34.710
What a foolish dream

761
00:23:35.600 --> 00:23:36.680
...we looked to

762
00:23:36.680 --> 00:23:40.390
Shining a light on paths that no one's ever tread down

763
00:23:40.390 --> 00:23:44.470
Get up, on our feet and Try

764
00:23:44.470 --> 00:23:48.480
Let's see the ends of places no one's ever dreamed of

765
00:23:48.480 --> 00:23:52.280
Yeah, together we can all Fly
